fields.title: Cloud computing

fields.body:
Idea 1
I need to focus, I get it through music I like 
Information need: Music
Emo/Cog need: Focus/concentration/attention
However I can’t remember the name of the artists (“Made in Heights”)
10 years ago, I would have only had access to the records 
which I have at home. 5 years ago perhaps I wouldn’t be able 
to type the lyrics of a track and immediately get its artist.

What does this immediacy of information mean for our 
cognitive and emotional state or our expectations and perception 
of information?
For people born with search engines, would there be changes in behaviour if this immediacy was removed?

Idea 2
I spend a lot of time bookmarking things and organising and synthesising data
is that better than simply “refinding” the information?
